{"type":"message","id":"0ecfffd1","parentId":"d7aec758","timestamp":"2026-03-23T06:04:08.805Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_4r76jmtc6io8_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/bin/bash\nset -e\n\necho \"🚀 Nova Browser starting up...\"\n\n# Start Xvfb (virtual display :1, 1920x1080, 24bit color)\necho \"📺 Starting virtual display...\"\nXvfb :1 -screen 0 1920x1080x24 &\nXVFB_PID=$!\nexport DISPLAY=:1\n\nsleep 1\n\n# Start OpenBox (lightweight window manager)\necho \"🪟 Starting window manager...\"\nopenbox &\nsleep 1\n\n# Start Chrome with remote debugging + no-sandbox\necho \"🌐 Starting Chrome...\"\ngoogle-chrome \\\n    --no-sandbox \\\n    --disable-gpu \\\n    --disable-dev-shm-usage \\\n    --remote-debugging-port=9222 \\\n    --remote-debugging-address=0.0.0.0 \\\n    --kiosk \\\n    --app=https://www.google.com \\\n    &\n\nCHROME_PID=$!\nsleep 2\n\n# Start x11vnc (share the X display)\necho \"🔗 Starting VNC server...\"\nx11vnc -display :1 -nopw -listen localhost -xkb -ncache 10 -ncache_cr -forever -shared -rfbport 5900 &\n\nsleep 1\n\n# Start noVNC (WebSocket-to-VNC proxy on port 8080)\necho \"🖥️  Starting noVNC...\"\ncd /usr/share/novnc && ./utils/launch.sh --vnc localhost:5900 --listen 8080 &\n\nsleep 1\n\necho \"\"\necho \"✅ Nova Browser is live!\"\necho \"   noVNC (browser view):  http://localhost:8080/vnc.html\"\necho \"   Chrome DevTools:       http://localhost:9222\"\necho \"\"\n\n# Keep container alive\nwait\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774245848796}}
{"type":"message","id":"d037c013","parentId":"0ecfffd1","timestamp":"2026-03-23T06:04:08.816Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_4r76jmtc6io8_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# syntax=docker/dockerfile:1.4\nFROM ubuntu:22.04\n\nENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive\n\n# Install Chrome, xvfb, VNC, noVNC, OpenBox\nRUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y \\\n    wget \\\n    gnupg2 \\\n    ca-certificates \\\n    apt-transport-https \\\n    unzip \\\n    xauth \\\n    xvfb \\\n    libdbus-1-3 \\\n    libasound2 \\\n    libatk1.0-0 \\\n    libatk-bridge2.0-0 \\\n    libcups2 \\\n    libdrm2 \\\n    libxkbcommon0 \\\n    libxcomposite1 \\\n    libxdamage1 \\\n    libxfixes3 \\\n    libxrandr2 \\\n    libgbm1 \\\n    libpango-1.0-0 \\\n    libcairo2 \\\n    libatspi2.0-0 \\\n    libsecret-1-0 \\\n    openbox \\\n    x11vnc \\\n    websockify \\\n    novnc \\\n    && apt-get clean \\\n    && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\n\n# Install Chrome (latest stable)\nRUN wget -q -O /tmp/chrome.deb https://dl.google.com/linux/chrome/deb/pool/main/g/google-chrome-stable/google-chrome-stable_$(wget -q -O - https://dl.google.com/linux/chrome/deb/dists/stable/release.basesql | grep -oP 'Version: \\K[^ ]+' | head -1)_amd64.deb \\\n    && apt-get install -y /tmp/chrome.deb \\\n    && rm /tmp/chrome.deb\n\n# Copy startup script\nCOPY startup.sh /startup.sh\nRUN chmod +x /startup.sh\n\nEXPOSE 8080 5900 9222\n\nCMD [\"/startup.sh\"]\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774245848806}}
{"type":"message","id":"3d7802b7","parentId":"d037c013","timestamp":"2026-03-23T06:04:18.842Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, so:\n1. **Nova UI** - a custom web chat UI (FastAPI + HTML/CSS/JS) at `C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\nova-ui\\`. The backend runs on port 8765.\n2. **Nova Browser** - a Docker container that runs Chrome in a headless virtual display with VNC/noVNC for browser automation.\n\nNow, \"the chrome work together thing\" - this is probably about connecting Nova UI with Nova Browser (Chrome automation). So you could control Chrome from within Nova UI.\n\nLet me start Nova UI backend first and see if it works. The backend is at `C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\nova-ui\\backend\\main.py`.\n\n\nI need to get Nova UI running first, then figure out how to wire it up with Nova Browser. Zach probably wants them communicating through the OpenClaw gateway, maybe using CDP for Chrome control or just running the browser container and connecting everything through there.","thinkingSignature":"d0505ed0923d3e21167e38cbadd9db2d538f0b56d865512e622ceb9528544762"},{"type":"text","text":"Got it — `nova-ui` is our custom web UI (FastAPI backend + sleek frontend) and `nova-browser` is the Chrome-in-Docker setup with VNC. Let me get both running.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_pr8p37gswgiv_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\nova-ui\\backend && python main.py","background":true,"elevated":false}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":17233,"output":314,"cacheRead":13506,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":31053,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774245848817}}
