{"type":"message","id":"cf37c77b","parentId":"221eb0cf","timestamp":"2026-03-23T06:13:01.286Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, so the gateway token is `05a9121e8d27e2ca7f90ec7bab2ddd6b1b111b761aac0fc0` and the gateway is running on port 18789. The backend in `main.py` uses this same token.\n\nNow let me check what endpoints are available on the gateway. The backend is trying to hit `/v1/responses` which is OpenAI-compatible. But the gateway config shows:\n```json\n\"http\": {\n  \"endpoints\": {\n    \"responses\": {\n      \"enabled\": true\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nSo `/v1/responses` should be enabled. Let me test that endpoint directly.","thinkingSignature":"6f4f608db03ce416463d6b781aa9a2a13e3c7127510a1ccbcd281010cb7b7058"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jnsypbkzr0c8_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -X POST http://127.0.0.1:18789/v1/responses -H \"Authorization: Bearer 05a9121e8d27e2ca7f90ec7bab2ddd6b1b111b761aac0fc0\" -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"model\":\"openclaw:main\",\"input\":[{\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"test\"}],\"stream\":false}' 2>&1 | head -30","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":21078,"output":288,"cacheRead":13506,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":34872,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774246366319}}
